The paper deals with the stable marriage problem, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of approximation ratios and the focus on finding a largest stable matching suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the theory of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the consideration of strategy-proofness against coalitions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
